    "Obtain output y j from LLM 5: end for 6: Send set {y j } to the aggregation module 7: Obtain the confidence score c 8: return c",
    "To encapsulate epistemic uncertainties, our focus shifts towards understanding the susceptibility of model outputs to minor perturbations.",
    "Existing methods introduce perturbations using Monte Carlo Dropout (Seeböck et al., 2019; Tuna et al., 2022; Gal and Ghahramani, 2016).",
    "However, this approach is not feasible for closed LLM APIs.",
    "As an alternative, we introduce perturbations to the model inputs: the temperature and the prompt."
